news.headline: New data points to 'stable' job market amid 'low layoffs, low quits'
news.summary: Economic data out Wednesday showed the pace of hiring in the US economy continued to slow. But separate data indicated layoffs remain low, keeping the US labor market in a 'no hire, no fire' stasis.

news.headline: U.S. Corporate Bankruptcies Hit 14-Year High
news.summary: US corporate bankruptcies have hit their highest levels since the GFC. Investors need to keep our eye on the ball. Plunging financials may indicate that you need to dispose of an investment.

news.headline: Why Nvidia rug pull doesn't faze US stock market bulls: Morning Brief
news.summary: Nvidia's 6% loss Tuesday was especially painful for the company given it followed a splashy CES event with big announcements. But the market has good reason to shake off its swings.

news.headline: Don't Buy SPY
news.summary: The S&P 500's forward P/E ratio suggests a 0% return over the next decade; consider selling it for better alternatives. Learn more about SPY here.

news.headline: Rates Are Rising For The Right Reason, So Don't Panic
news.summary: Stocks are adjusting to yield curve normalization, not inflation fears. Job openings and ISM Services PMI rise suggest healthy economic growth. Read the full market outlook on Seeking Alpha.
